# .aidocs/project-update.aidocs - /project-update Contract

Purpose
- Sync project-local AI system files to latest canonical versions without re-running full initialization.

When to use
- Use `/project-update` for projects that already ran `/project-init` and only need system/runtime refresh.

Source resolution (!!!):
- AIDOCS source path MUST be read from the global routing file (`~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` or `~/.config/opencode/AGENTS.md`), which contains `AIDOCS source: <path>`.
- Never compute, search, or guess the source path. The installer `.cmd` is the sole authority that sets this path.

Contract
- Validate project is already initialized (`/.MEMORY/` + router present).
- Copy/sync project-local system artifacts from AIDOCS source:
  - `.aidocs/index.aidocs`
  - linked shared docs
  - `.aidocs/personalities/` directory (all personality definition files)
- Refresh project `AGENTS.md` and `CLAUDE.md` with project-local relative routes in this order: `/.MEMORY/INDEX.md`, `/.MEMORY/NOW.md`, `.aidocs/index.aidocs`.
- Copy missing memory template files; for routing-critical memory files, normalize managed routing text without overwriting project-specific facts.
- Copy missing `/agents/` template files from `.aidocs/templates/agents/**`.
- Regenerate Claude Code auto-memory file:
  - Resolve Claude projects directory: `~/.claude/projects/`.
  - Prefer updating existing project folders whose normalized name matches the current project root.
  - If no existing folder is found, create deterministic candidate folders from the current project root using both drive-letter variants (for example `e--Projects-Tools-AutoDeployBase` and `E--Projects-Tools-AutoDeployBase`) and use the first candidate.
  - Target file: `~/.claude/projects/<resolved>/memory/MEMORY.md` (create parent directories if missing).
  - This file is auto-loaded into every Claude Code session's system prompt.
  - Rewrite the file as redirect-only bootstrap content.
  - It must point to `<project>/.MEMORY/INDEX.md` first and `<project>/.MEMORY/NOW.md` second.
  - It must explicitly forbid storing memory, plans, summaries, or task output there.
  - It must direct spawned-agent plans/investigations to `<project>/agents/` using `YYYY-MM-DD-<topic>-plan.md` or `YYYY-MM-DD-<topic>-investigation.md`.
  - Do not preserve side content; the file is not a secondary memory surface.
  - MEMORY.md is READ-ONLY during normal sessions — only `/project-update` writes managed content.
- Do not run ingestion/restructuring/topic-map rebuild unless explicitly requested.
- Include command pack version from `.aidocs/command-pack.version` in the sync report when available.
- Commands are global-only; do not sync `.opencode/command/*` or `.claude/commands/*` into projects.
- Include global command-pack health in report (source path + expected global command presence).
- Include related-project memory status in report (`/.MEMORY/related-projects/FIXES_BY_OTHER_AGENTS.md` present).
- Hard gate after sync: re-read updated project routing/instructions before continuing any other task:
  1) `AGENTS.md` and/or `CLAUDE.md`
  2) `/.MEMORY/INDEX.md`
  3) `/.MEMORY/NOW.md`
  4) `.aidocs/index.aidocs`
  5) linked shared docs from the index
  This applies in the same session (no restart required).

Safety
- Re-read `/.MEMORY/INDEX.md` first, then `/.MEMORY/NOW.md`, before planning and after compaction/session resume.
- Log update outcome to today's daily file.
